The use of web-conferencing in the college of veterinary medicine at Washington State University. This article presents a review of Web-conferencing and evaluation data from veterinary students and animal owners participating in Web-conference events. Web-conferencing allowed for high-fidelity transmission of images and adequate transmission of audio by off-site instructors. Geographically distributed participants found Web-conference software easy to set up and to use. Participant satisfaction varied with the type of participant the highest satisfaction rate was from pet owners and the lowest from veterinary students in a core course.